, 1683. She married John Wilson on July 4, 1683 — twenty-seven days later. The marriage had presumably been planned before his death, but she wed her cousin in the immediate shadow of her father's loss."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Inherited 150 Farmington acres from her father","body":"Her father Roger Newton Sr.'s 1683 will left her 150 acres in 'Bohemia' Farmington. Family tradition speculates the land may have originally been given to her mother Mary Hooker by Governor Haynes — connecting it to the Hartford founding generation."}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"artworks":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Sarah Newton Wilson","first_name":"Sarah","last_name":"Wilson","married_names":["Wilson"],"maiden_name":"Newton"},"documents":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"sarah-wilson-1662"},"X00015":{"id":"X00015","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":true},"birth":{"year":1663,"state":"Massachusetts"},"death":{"year":1727},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X00016","children_ids":["I00015"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1686}],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 15"},{"short":"NHA — Oldest House / Jethro Coffin House","url":"https://nha.org/visit/historic-sites/oldest-house/"}],"gender":"male","parents":{"father_id":"X03179","mother_id":"X03180"},"tags":[],"number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":[],"primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jethro_Coffin_House","primary_url_label":"Wikipedia","notable_blurb":"Builder of Nantucket's oldest surviving house"},"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"X02352","display_label":"Grandfather who founded Nantucket settlement in 1659","link_text":"Tristram Coffin Sr."}],"bio":{"display_name":"Jethro Coffin","first_name":"Jethro","last_name":"Coffin","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"rese